The paper discusses the interactions between humans and data, which is a core topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). It also touches on the social and ethical implications of data collection and use, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the technical challenges of managing and analyzing large amounts of data, which is a core topic in databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the interdisciplinary nature of the topic, which could potentially fall under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
